The property is located between King & Market Streets on the eastern side of Clarence Street. Access to King Street Wharf, QVB and Town Hall Station including the lightrail are only minutes away by foot.

The style and quality of 156 Clarence Street is underlined by the fact that one of Sydney's leading architectural firms, Gray Pucksand, is headquartered in the building. Further enhancing the tenancy profile is the strong retail component, including one of Sydney's premium bars The Baxter Inn.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
60 Castlereagh is one of Sydney’s premier office buildings located at the heart of the Sydney CBD’s business, retail, and leisure epicentre. 

The 20-storey A-grade building is in an enviable location, with easy access to Martin Place, St James and Town Hall stations, and is surrounded by bustling cafés, bars, food courts, fine dining restaurants, shops and arts and culture venues. The trendy Verandah Bar and Social@Verandah are located on the Mezzanine, having recently undergone an extensive facelift, offering a convenient location for business and social occasions. 

The building’s efficient central core provides flexible, column-free floor plates, while the curved windows make the most of sweeping views across Sydney Harbour from the top four floors. 

End-of-trip facilities including bicycle racks, change rooms, lockers and showers are currently being upgraded and due to be completed Q3 2020. 

Additional key features include a 5-star NABERS Energy rating, 24/7 on-site security and a fully automated building management and control system, basement parking and an exciting lobby refurbishment planned.

Current availabilities include:
- Level 3 - 1,677sqm, expansive whole floor with two large balconies and existing fit-out
- Level 9 – 1,142sqm, whole floor featuring existing fit-out and two large balconies
- Level 10 – 1,105sqm, whole floor featuring existing fit-out 

Dexus is and has always been the space for your best work. That means space that’s clean and safe. In keeping with advice from the government and leading industry bodies, namely Safe Work Australia, we’ve increased our hygiene measures and made significant changes to the way people move through and interact in our spaces in order to adhere to social distancing rules.

In time, we will reopen our signature services of priority childcare, wellness programs, end-of-trip facilities and exclusive events. For now, our focus is on ensuring that we’re providing the cleanest, safest spaces possible for our communities.
